profile_positions.description:
- Owning the end-to-end process for timely availability of product data, from PLM to SAP, PIM and sell-in tools;
- Responsible for pricing upload in SAP, updating pricing files, price master change log and logic;
- Continuously managing timeline deadlines, monitoring status, and aligning with stakeholders;
- Set up, track, and maintenance of KPI reporting to create visibility of current performance;
- Overseeing operational activities of Coordinators to guard efficiency and alignment;
- Reassessing the team’s operational procedures & tools and highlights & drive improvement opportunities together with the Senior Manager;
- Working closely with Coordinators to identify opportunities to improve the efficiency of cross-functional activities, systems, and tools;
- Building and maintaining relationships with internal stakeholders to create an efficient and on-time product data delivery and to ensure optimization of all reporting and processes;
- Managing a team of 3 Coordinators by setting team priorities, providing feedback on personal development, performance review and managing operational matters;
- Developing Dashboards in Tableau to oversee the team KPIs;
- 3 Direct reports;

- Ensured timely availability of interfaced PLM product data across SAP/PIM and WeConnect, by continuously monitoring and aligning product data;
- Maintained selling tool visibility of product data in PIM;
-  Set up, tracked, and maintained of reports;
- Managed key milestones to ensure Product Data is aligned as needed;
- Took the lead on cross-divisional topics which apply to the internal team and ensures alignment & follow-up within the team are applied;
- Developed and maintained strong relationships with central, divisional, and cross-divisional teams to create an efficient and aligned set-up of Product Data across various systems and to ensure optimization of all external Product Data related reporting and processes;
- Performed requirements analysis and reports upon requests;
- Supported the manager by reassessing the team’s operational procedures & tools and highlighting improvement opportunities.
- Supported the manager in the operational implementation of solutions and improvements with the teams involved.
- Searched for solutions to improve inefficient processes.
- Shared operational knowledge and best practices to participate in the team effort to raise working efficiency.

- Ensured correctness and timely availability of product data in all systems for sell-in season;
- Set up all systems and master files relevant for product data storage (PLM, PIM, SAP/FMS, WeConnect);
- Managed product data deadlines by liaising with Product Merchandising and Product Development;
- Managed interfacing between systems (PLM, PIM, SAP, WeConnect) and uploaded prices for all EU product data;
- Ensured continuous alignment and accurate data across systems by tracking changes, (cross-) checking data, and updating data across all systems;
- Provided (ad hoc) reporting and analysis with regards to prices and KPIs, to stakeholders (e.g. Product Merchandising, Market Merchandising, Product Development, Buying and Planning);
- Developed and maintained strong relationships with Product Development and Merchandising by providing continuous training and information updates (e.g. pre-season refreshment course, feedback sessions, and information meetings) regarding PLM and additional relevant systems;
- Proactively highlighted and followed up on any issues which may arise during the process by maintaining close contact with your direct team members and manager;
- Developed and updated processes and training materials;
- Developed macros and power queries, automating our Master Files;

- Executed effective social media content-focused digital marketing strategies to build brand awareness; 
- Managed the company brand in line with brand guidelines.
- Executed in-house digital marketing activity;
- Monitored social media marketing activities, content marketing, social media marketing, and paid advertising; 
- Artwork creation in Photoshop and Final Cut - such as digital media, and others;
- Managed direct marketing activities including ads campaigns and offers, using Facebook Ads Manager platform to organize data and to evaluate effectiveness;
- Identified and share opportunities for improving the value of digital marketing for our business with a strong focus on ROI;
- Managed budget and campaign following all internal policy and procedures;

-	Display a strong bias in doing what’s right for the client’s community in supporting the client's mission;
-	Gather, analyze and utilize relevant data to develop ways to improve the overall user experience on the site;
-	Use market-specific knowledge, signals, and insights to spot and scope scalable solutions to improve the support of our community of users;
-	Recognize trends and patterns within large data sets, and escalate issues outside the company policy to the global team as they arise;
-	Respond to disputes with high quality, speed, empathy, and accuracy;
-	Identify inefficiencies in workflows and suggest solutions, work well within a team environment and effectively implement policies;
-      Developed different strategies to improve team accuracy; 
-	Responsible for creating and developing training decks for new hires;

- Delivered excellent customer service to Bloomberg customers and internal departments to make the information comparable to investors around the world who use Bloomberg Terminal make the right investment decisions;
- Researched and analyzed financial data of a portfolio of companies across the various products & geographies for Bloomberg´s Fundamentals product;
 - Provided accurate and reliable demographic and statistical financial market data to an internal database and internal/external clientele;
- Analyzed financial statements and ratios from various sources: 8K, 10Q, others upon request; 
- Maintained the quality of the database from a macro perspective and ensure the efficiency of the data management workflow to reach the highest level of timeliness and accuracy to Bloomberg clients;

-	Managed accounts and developed solutions for public figures and media publishers on social media platforms (Facebook and Instagram) Markets supported: global;
-	Assessed and improved workflows to scale out support for internal and external requests;
-	Designed and improved internal procedures manuals increasing support and bringing Dublin headquarters to be the primary project for public users and verifications;
-	Worked with media partners (A+/A tier), providing assistance, collecting feedback and managing communication to improve product experiences; 
-	Created and developed training manuals for new hires, identifying training needs by evaluating strengths and weakness during training sessions;
-	Point of contact to increase support for public users, develop and implement workflow to partners resulting in an 80% increase over the previous year Turn Around Time;
-	Top of the team in KPI and winner of the most productive of the team award;

-	Responsible for working in all areas of Food and Beverage as needed to deliver an excellent Guest and Member experience;
-      Taking daily pictures of all bar social media;
-	Cash management;
-	Managed guest queries in a timely and efficient manner;
-	One of the top 10 of the team in personal sales; 
-	Consistently achieved monthly targets;

-	Developed functional process workflows based on the department need;
-	Supported the development of a new system responsible for all workflow regarding music licensing and determine requirements for the process; 
-	Created training decks for new employees; 
-	Pitched, negotiated, prepared and account managed synchronization licenses (music rights) for all media copyright contracts around worldwide territories including OTT;
-       Achieved monthly Revenue sales KPI’s.
-	Handled high priority deals before deadline to maintain a healthy forecast;
-       Achieved annual target with 2 months before the end of fiscal year and lead top priority deals between America Latina and World Wide;
-	Managed full sales cycle;
-	Coordinated information between various departments;
